msgstr ""

#: /__w/calibre/calibre/src/calibre/ebooks/conversion/plugins/epub_output.py:135
msgid ""
"The version of the EPUB file to generate. EPUB 2 is the most widely "
"compatible, only use EPUB 3 if you know you actually need it."
msgstr ""

#: /__w/calibre/calibre/src/calibre/ebooks/conversion/plugins/epub_output.py:604
msgid ""
"Split all HTML files larger than this size (in KB). This is necessary as "
"some devices cannot handle large file sizes. Set to 0 to disable size based "
"splitting."
msgstr ""

#: /__w/calibre/calibre/src/calibre/ebooks/conversion/plugins/epub_output.py:615
msgid ""
"The KEPUB renderer on the Kobo has a bug when text justification is turned "
"on. It will either not justify text properly or when highlighting there will"
" be gaps between neighboring highlighted parts of text. By default, calibre "
"generates KEPUB that avoid the highlighting gaps at the expense of worse "
"text justification. This option reverses that tradeoff. Use this option if "
"you use justification when reading on your Kobo device."
msgstr ""

#: /__w/calibre/calibre/src/calibre/ebooks/conversion/plugins/epub_output.py:624
msgid ""
"Modify how hyphenation is performed for this book. Note that hyphenation "
"does not perform well for all languages, as it depends on the dictionaries "
"present on the device, which are not always of the highest quality."
msgstr ""

